          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Evaporated Sn targets with typical thickness of 500",
                "ug/cm2. The targets were prepared on 93Nb or 165Ho",
                "catcher foils of 2.5 mg/cm2 thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 1000 um Si surface barrier detectors,",
                "placed at +/- 20 degrees with respect to the beam",
                "axis to monitor beam intensity"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Si(Li) detectors with diameter of 16 mm,",
                "and an active thickness of 5 mm were used for",
                "activity measurements. Both detectors had 50 microns",
                "thick Be windows, and were surrounded by 5 cm thick",
                "lead shielding."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA",
                "ACTIV",
                "EDEG",
                "XSPEC",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam first",
                "crossed a thin Au foil (100 ug/cm2) before hitting",
                "the target. Both single target and stacked target",
                "irradiations were used to measure the excitation",
                "function of 6Li + 120Sn and 7Li + 119Sn. In both",
                "cases, the compound nucleus 126I is created, which",
                "produces 124I and 123I isotopes via 2n and 3n",
                "evaporation channels. Both isotopes then decay via EC",
                "into tellurium, which is followed by emission of",
                "atomic x-ray lines.",
                "In addition, production cross sections for 120Sb were",
                "also measured by detecting the characteristic x-rays",
                "of Sn."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In the analysis, only the k-alpha lines of Te and Sb",
                "were used, taking into account the corresponding",
                "fluorescence probabilities. The yields were",
                "determined from the analysis of the measured activity",
                "as function of the time."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
